This paper deals with improving the performance of neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of Word2Vec embeddings, which is a popular technique in machine learning and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study also involves the use of attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in deep learning and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of bidirectional encoder attention decoder models, which is a common technique in neural networks and falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of morphological segmentation, which is a common technique in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
